Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, scallion whites, 1 cup water, @harissa powder{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 cups water and 1 tsp harissa powder.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While bulgur cooks, open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with @harissa powder{1/2%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use more or less harissa powder depending on spice tolerance. Reserve any remaining for another use.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Keep covered off heat until ready to assemble sandwiches.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, a pinch of scallion greens, and a pinch of parsley. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with pepper.

Halve and toast @brioche buns{2}.

Trim and finely dice @mini cucumber{1}.

Cut @tomato{1} into rounds; reserve four rounds for sandos and dice remaining rounds into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Drain any excess water from bulgur; fluff with a fork. Stir in lemon zest, a large drizzle of @olive oil{3%teaspoon}, and juice from half the lemon.

Add cucumber, diced tomato, and remaining scallion greens; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Spread herby crema on bottom halves of buns. Top with chicken and tomato rounds. Close sandos.

Divide sandos and bulgur salad between plates. Garnish salad with remaining parsley. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.